info.title: Verified Inc. API
info.description: Collection of requests to facilitate interfacing with the Verified Inc. API.

post.description: Checks if credentials of the specified type(s) exist for the specified user identifiers.

201.description: success (no match) / success (match) / success: hasMatchingCredentials (no match) / success: hasMatchingCredentials w/ partnerUuid / success: hasMatchingCredentials (no match) / success: hasMatchingCredentials w/o partnerUuid

tags.description: Our schema API facilitates programmatically validating schemas and getting schema attribute descriptions.

tags.name: Integration Test Suite
tags.description:
A folder of requests to facilitate testing your integration. Whether you an Acceptor or an Issuer, this folder can be used for testing during development or for regressions. This particluarly useful to get a sense for the UX during development.

The existing `issuerBrandApiKey` and `acceptorBrandApiKey` are that of Hooli and Kredita. You only need to replace for whichever role you would like to test for.

Please note, to test the Partner flow with your brand specific API key you need to update the `partnerUuid` variable. However, additionally, some further configurations maybe needed. Please reach out to us to get you setup to test with the test brands, Hooli and/or Kredita.
